---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Solana Saga Phone Launch 2022 — AES" bodyClass="inner-page">

  <div class="container-fluid event-hero">
    <div class="event-hero-inner">
      <div class="event-hero-left">
        <div class="event-location">New York City, USA</div>
        <div class="event-title">Solana<br />Saga Phone<br />Launch<br />2022</div>
        <div class="event-tagline">
          Solana approached our agency less than 30 days out from the Saga phone launch to produce the big reveal at the New York Times Center. No lead time… no problem.
        </div>
        <div class="event-hero-photo">
          <div class="event-hero-photo-item" style="background-image: url('/images/work1.png')"></div>
          <div class="event-hero-photo-item" style="background-image: url('/images/work2.png')"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="event-hero-right">
        <div class="event-detail-card">
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">The Brief</div>
            <p>With under 30 days to execute, Solana tapped us to produce the live reveal event for the Saga — their debut Web3 smartphone. The venue was the New York Times Center, a world-class auditorium that demanded a production approach worthy of a major product launch.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">Production</div>
            <p>Compressed timelines require decisive planning. We secured the venue, assembled the production team, and built out the full technical rider — staging, LED, lighting, and AV — in a fraction of the time a typical product launch would allow. Every decision had to be right the first time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">On-Site Highlights</div>
            <p>The reveal landed exactly as intended — a packed auditorium, a dramatic stage moment, and a product that instantly generated global buzz. The event set the tone for Saga's public debut and proved that great work doesn't require months of runway.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid event-gallery">
    <div class="event-gallery-inner">
      <div class="gallery-grid">
        <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large" style="background-image: url('/images/work3.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder" style="background-image: url('/images/work5.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder" style="background-image: url('/images/work7.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large" style="background-image: url('/images/work9.png')"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid event-back">
    <div class="event-back-inner">
      <a href="/work" class="cr-btn white ex-padding">← Back to All Events</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
